### 2. Deduplicate Sort Logic on Dashboard
The task sorting logic (criticality ‚Üí in_progress ‚Üí due_date ‚Üí priority) is duplicated verbatim in [page.tsx](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/app/page.tsx) lines 166‚Äì181 and again in [refreshTasks()](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/app/page.tsx#261-287) at lines 265‚Äì283. There's also a [taskSort.ts](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/lib/taskSort.ts) utility already, but the dashboard doesn't use it.

**Fix**: Consolidate all sorting into [lib/taskSort.ts](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/lib/taskSort.ts) and import everywhere.

### 3. Type Inconsistencies
- `TimetableSlot.id` is `number` in the dashboard but `string | number` in the timetable page
- [Assignment](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/models/assignment.py#8-48) type is defined separately in [page.tsx](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/app/page.tsx) (dashboard), [assignments/page.tsx](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/app/assignments/page.tsx), and [announcements/page.tsx](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/app/announcements/page.tsx) ‚Äî each with different fields
- No shared type definitions between pages

**Fix**: Create a `lib/types.ts` with canonical types shared across all pages.

### 4. Backend Timestamp Inconsistency
- [Task](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/app/focus/page.tsx#8-15) model uses `Asia/Singapore` timezone via [_now_sg()](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/models/task.py#10-12)
- [Assignment](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/models/assignment.py#8-48) model uses `datetime.utcnow` (UTC)
- These are in the same DB, which could cause confusing comparisons

**Fix**: Standardize on Singapore timezone everywhere (per your GEMINI.md rule).

